Golf Park's David Wakhu final score of  seven under par 277 at Kenya Savannah Classic was lowest by any Kenyan playing in the event in the countryFor making the cut in addition to cash reward from KBL, the two excelling local pros earned almost Sh1m combinedNjoroge finished in 77th place in the Magical Kenya Open which was staged as a European Tour event for the second time In addition to earning prize money after making the cut at the Kenya Savannah Classic and Magical Kenya Open, local professionals  David Wakhu and Samuel Njoroge also received individual cash awards from Kenya Breweries Limited, the presenting sponsor of the Magical Kenya Open through its top spirit brand Johnnie Walker. 



